South Africans woke up to the news that Dr Judy Dlamini has been appointed the first black female Chancellor of the University of the Witwatersrand Dlamini will take over from former Deputy Chief Justice Dikgang Moseneke on 1 December as the Chancellor of one of the best universities on the continent. READ MORE: Dr Judy Dlamini’s history-making new role After the university announced the news last night, Dlamini’s phone must have been ringing off the hook from well-wishers sending her their congratulatory messages. Others took to social media to send the medical doctor, businesswoman and author their well-wishes.    